    <note>Fang(1) Shenyan [600] According to his uncle Yi's [3297] biography, their ancestors were Shejun Fang(1). Yi's grandfather, who was probably a lineal descendant of Hong [16931], moved to Xinghua jun, Putian xian, probably from Yanzhou, Chunan county. Yi and Shenyan both earned the jinshi in 1000. Fang(1) Shide [3300], the son-in-law of Ye(1) Yong's [2058] fourth generation ancestor, Ye(1) Bin [4072], was probably a member of the same generation of a cadet branch of Shenyan's lineage. Jiangxi TZ, 13.3a; Fujian TZ, 147.6a; Guangdong TZ, 14.24b. CBD, 1, 84.</note>
